node.text:
Probably one of the craziest experiences I’ve had while bass fishing. Watching a giant school swim around and eat everything in sight! This is a trip in the @nativewatercraft I won’t forget anytime soon. 

📷: @the_trevorsoety

node.text: Flogging- seems to be a lot of controversy on this. This is not a new thing, it’s been around for along time. First time I have ever used one was this past week. Its not easy to use when the wind is blowing, it’s a ton of work. It’s made for seeing smallmouth on there beds which are usually in 6-12 foot. It works so good on the St Lawrence and Great Lakes bc 1. Water is gin clear 2. Smallmouth are not nearly as spookie , you can literally have your boat over the top of them when bed fishing 3. Cuts glare off water so you can see if the bait is on the bed which is super hard to do if it’s deep. It was a lot of fun this past week, finished 15th. Thanks Flogger!!
